<br>
Finally, this Hypnos was getting what he deserved. Gaia nodded to Athena in respinse to her words. She was keeping her words to minimum, Justice wasn't her realm.<br>
 <p>~*-:¦:-*~Gaia: Greek Goddess of Earth~*-:¦:-*~ <BR>-§Mother Earth§-¤Mother of the Titans¤-¥Mother of All Creation¥-</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uthegreatapollo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>The Great Apollo</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.maialino.it/musica/bsb_nick.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 178<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(7/7/02 2:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=260.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.efanguide.com/~hayden/gallery/misc/hayden28.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Excellent</span><hr size=1> Apollo laughed and clapped his hands giddily from his thrown like a child. He loved the fast paced drama that unfolded everyday upon Olympus, it was a wonder how he did without it for several months. He shook the hair from his azure eyes, his angelic smile playing on his face. Taking a truffle from the pounch on his tunic, he threw it in his mouth and stood up, taking a sip of nectar.<br>
<br>
&quot;I agree, that Hypnos should be punished. But Athena I disagree with you that he should just be punished without trial. It is an unalienable right of man and god to defend himself before a court of his peers. We shall assemble a tribunal, to judge the trial and a prosecutor to question Hypnos and his comrades. Let no one ever say that the god's are a bunch of uncivilized feinds who punish eachother without due course.&quot;<br>
<br>
Apollo's eyes moved from person to person as he spoke.<br>
<br>
&quot;Let us not abuse our power as Olympians. For as Olympians we have a duty to make an example for the rest of the gods and for mankind. The abuse of power would upset the balance which is already dangerously tottering on the brink tyranny up on these heavenly peaks of Olympus our home. The gods are at the appex of the universal triangle, and we must use our power for the greater good.&quot;<br>
<br>
He bowed his head, graciously. Always the eloquent speaker, Apollo hoped that his words would hit his seniors in such a way that they would conscider his proposition for a proper trial. With this he sat back down in his throne. <p>     *~*The Golden God*~*
