<br>
&quot;Of course he shall have a trial before his peers. I said bring him to me . . . and it shall be done. But no matter, he shall be found guilty of one thing or another. For he has surely caused a disturbance among us and has charged war against the amazons. He shall defend himself or have someone do it for him, and in the end we shall decide guilty or innocent, and the sentance of punishment will be given.&quot;<br>
<br>
She took another sip from her chalice. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uposeidonkofc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Poseidonkofc</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Golden Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 314<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(7/8/02 7:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=260.topic&index=24>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://web.uvic.ca/grs/bowman/myth/images/haifa/h89.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Justice</span><hr size=1> &quot;Well the decision being thus as is appointed by all the adherents here pertaining to the trail of Hypnos and the others of his like, let it commence.&quot; said the sea god after all had agreed and awaited the next appointment.<br>
<br>
Poseidon clapped his hands together two times and all those who were to deal with what was just discussed were transported by his power to an open grove in Greece, where the flowers grew wild. Those who sat in their thrones were upon thrones in likeness and those who stood were standing there in the tall green grasses.<br>
<br>
Poseidon looked around and lastly to Athena. &quot;Who shall bring the criminals here bound in shackles?&quot; And then he turned to Apollo, &quot;Though the trial will be held, the guilty cannot hope to waylay their guilt but they shall in a civilized manner have a right to be proven guilty which they shall.&quot;<br>
<br>
His crown reflected the suns light brightly in the all but empty grove. <p>Poseidon~Lord of the Deep Blue Sea~Patron Of Horses And Sailors~</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/ugaiaofearth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gaia of Earth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 47<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(7/8/02 10:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=260.topic&index=25>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://hometown.aol.com/thegooddochl6/images/gaia12.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Trial</span><hr size=1> Since, Hypnos sent one of his men forth to destroy and flame the Earth that the Amazons lived on, Gaia was one who was transported to the site of the trial.<br>
<br>
She had been sitting on a bench in the Olympian throne room but when she was transported she made a large throne-like chair appear beneath her.<br>
<br>
There she sat, The Great Gaia awaiting Justice. <p>~*-:¦:-*~Gaia: Greek Goddess of Earth~*-:¦:-*~ <BR>-§Mother Earth§-¤Mother of the Titans¤-¥Mother of All Creation¥-</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=goddessathena>Goddess Athena</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 103<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(7/9/02 4:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=260.topic&index=26>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Bringers of Doom</span><hr size=1> Athena grinned lightly and turned her eyes to Poseidon.<br>
<br>
&quot;Let your followers search for him on land and sea, and when he is found I have the perfect people to bring him forth.&quot;<br>
