<br>
&quot;Just what I had hoped for.&quot;<br>
<br>
She turned and then looked to a corner of shadows and grinned. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/utheerinyes.showPublicProfile?language=EN>The Erinyes</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 104<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(7/11/02 5:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=260.topic&index=32>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Back in Action</span><hr size=1> Within the darkened shadows, a blaze of red, blue and black flames errupted out of the mist that lay there previously. Olympus itself seemed to darken. <br>
<br>
Alecto, Megaera and Tisiphone appeared wearing red strings. . .  and pretty much it.<br>
<br>
Alecto grinned as she swiftly came upon Hypnos as if she were Hermes himself. Hypnos was then tied down with chains of Hephaestus . .  Let's just say that Athena had access to them as of lately. Megaera grinned as she cuffed his hands down to the throne and Tisiphone stood there behind him ready to whisper at Athena's command.<br>
<br>
Most of the Gods knew of the Furies powers. Alecto was swifter and more clever than most, and unlike many Gods, she could freely travel to the Underworld at her leisure. Megaera could morph herself into the most beautiful of creatures, and the most hideous as well, her jealousy was like unto Hera's herself. And sweet Tisiphone whom loved her Mother Gaia so greatly, was the last to come from the blood of their Father. When thoughts of insanity bore in his mind, the youngest of the Furies was born with a curse. Her simple voice could drive the strongest of Gods to their limited sanity. The only one who could not fall into the insanity of Tisiphone's voice, was Gaia herself.<br>
<br>
After Hypnos had been detained, they all turned and smiled giving a bow to Gaia and a nod to Athena and Poseidon.<br>
<br>
Alecto then stepped forward.<br>
&quot;His trial may proceed, and we await orders for a punishment.&quot;<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/ugoddessartemis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Goddess Artemis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 366<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(7/11/02 5:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=260.topic&index=33>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Punishment</span><hr size=1> ~ Artemis sat back quietly through the whole thing. She wasnt even surprised when Hypnos showed with Poseidon's sleeping men. Naturally it would come to that, even her uncle did not have the power to stop the sleep. Zeus couldnt even stop it, and tho her uncle was almost as powerfull, he wasnt more powerfull then her father. Everyone knew how Artemis felt about Hypnos, and the reasons why. She nodded to Athena when she appeared, but said nothing,she would just watch.~ <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=hypnos>Hypnos </A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.backtalk.org/shadowydreamer/anime/zagato1.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Golden Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 302<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(7/11/02 10:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=260.topic&index=34>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Punishment</span><hr size=1> ***Hypnos had come here volentarily and he did not need the Erineyes rubbing it in for him, or even there little power to whisper things into Apollo, Athena, Posiedon, Artiemis, Gaia, or anyone elses ear... <br>
 <br>
Hypnos woke up a little from his sleepful thinking and gently blew into the air what almost looked like little fire flies that gave off a cloud of blue colored sparkling smoke. Each of these little things went to one of the Erineyes and swirled around them casting the spell of sleep over them, and making them fall into the ground, which suddenly had pillows to rest there head on.*** <p>~*Thè göd ö §|èèp ãñd Ïñspîråõñ.*~  
        </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uthegreatapollo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>The Great Apollo</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.maialino.it/musica/bsb_nick.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 180<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(7/11/02 2:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=260.topic&index=35>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> . . .</span><hr size=1> Apollo crossed his arms and watched as Hypnos made his spectacle. The very actions of throwing over the bench, and the dramatic dropping of the henchmen before Poseidon were all acts that have come to be extremely predictable and characteristic of Hypnos. The balance of hubris seemed to teeter on the brink of complete chaos inside of him. Apollo shook the hair from his eyes and smirked as the Eryines appeared in all their fury. The sun began to set in the western sky as the trial began to take place. His eyes shot to Hypnos who seemed to put on an air of indifference and meloncholy.<br>
<br>
&quot;Hypnos, do you not understand why you are here in the first place?&quot; He walked to Hypnos and took the hood from his head, slapping his cheek a bit to wake him out of his presistantly dozey mood.<br>
<br>
&quot;This disgusting display of your &quot;more holy than thou&quot; additude, where in this court it has no place is presicely why you are guilty of defying the universal law of hubris. You are in a court room of your superiors and still you continue to shamelessly flaunt your &quot;powers&quot; of sleep and illusion. Hypnos you have nothing to proove here today, we all have seen hundreds of times your deeds of sleep, and I would appreciate it if you did not use it against anyone in this court today. Grow up and stop acting like a godling. You made your bed, now lie in it.&quot; Apollo narrowed his eyes as he found himself playing the role of prosecutor.<br>
<br>
Apollo turned to Poseidon and Athena as nymphs tried their best at reviving the Erineyes. After phasing into a white toga which he felt was more appropriate for the matter he began to speak.<br>
<br>
&quot;Hypnos you are charged with several accounts of defying hubris. You are repeatedly found to be stepping your bounds as a minor god, taking situations out of your jurisdiction into your own hands and causing many a unneeded conflict upon the snowy cap of our home Mt. Olympus. Your foul sense of judgement and your insatiable appitite for mischeif has landed you before this tribunal here this evening. These acts are entirely seperate from the accounts of your unruly behavior during the Great Amazonian War of late. It has been brought to the attension of many Olympians that you and your motley crew of ruffians trounce around Greece causing nothing but chaos. Before you are prosecuted, I give you this time to argue in your defense. Though it would not do you much good, the crimes have been comitted but nevertheless you have the right to argue in your own name. Keep in mind you are arguing for yourself and the rest of your goons.&quot; Apollo said this with a bit of satisfaction in his voice, trying his best not to sound like a pedagogue. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=hypnos>Hypnos </A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.backtalk.org/shadowydreamer/anime/zagato1.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Golden Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 303<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(7/11/02 6:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=260.topic&index=36>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ...</span><hr size=1> ***Hypnos smirked and then sighed.*** <br>
 <br>
&quot;Apollo, Apollo, Apollo... If you think the whole situation over the Amazon civilization will disappear in a few centuries... In that time I could take a nap in that time. But the Amazons struck a nerve. They say its the Romans that turned them into what they are,they say that they want neutrality, but how can that be so when an assassin lives in every other hut. <br>
They should blame the gods, because if the gods love them so much they could of protected them from any of this happening....&quot; <br>
 <br>
(I'll write more later but my dad close the window and I had like four paragraphs and I'm just to frustrated to write it all back from memory right now, doesn't even sound right now &gt;.&lt;)  <p>~*Thè göd ö §|èèp ãñd Ïñspîråõñ.*~  
        </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/ugaiaofearth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gaia of Earth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 49<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(7/11/02 8:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=260.topic&index=37>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://hometown.aol.com/thegooddochl6/images/gaia12.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Her creations and children</span><hr size=1> Gaia suddenly beamed with pride as Alecto, Megaera and Tisiphone appeared. She gave a nod to them after they bowed. She kept silent so they could carry on with their duties.<br>
<br>
Gaia's eyes became furious when that @#%$ named Hypnos placed her children under his sleep realm. Her emerald orbs turned red and just as she was about to give a Hypnos a taste of her own power, something stopped her. <br>
<br>
She knew Hypnos would get his in the end. Alecto, Megaera and Tisiphone do their jobs well as Athena does.<br>
<br>
The Great Mother Goddess sat there silently, eyes calming from a raging fury. Hypnos thought he could get away with this, now not only had he tried to destroy the Earth but tried using his power against her creations and children. <p>~*-:¦:-*~Gaia: Greek Goddess of Earth~*-:¦:-*~ <BR>-§Mother Earth§-¤Mother of the Titans¤-¥Mother of All Creation¥-</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=hypnos>Hypnos </A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.backtalk.org/shadowydreamer/anime/zagato1.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Golden Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 304<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(7/11/02 10:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=260.topic&index=38>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Her creations and children</span><hr size=1> ***Hypnos looked at Gaia.***  <br>
 <br>
&quot;You accuse me of having a part in scorching you dear mother earth, but was it not Posiedon who tore your flesh?&quot; <p>~*Thè göd ö §|èèp ãñd Ïñspîråõñ.*~  
        </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/ugaiaofearth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gaia of Earth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 50<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(7/11/02 10:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=260.topic&index=39>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://hometown.aol.com/thegooddochl6/images/gaia12.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Earthy One</span><hr size=1> Gaia gave a short glance to Poseidon before setting her now cold eyes upon Hypnos.<br>
<br>
&quot;Poseidon is not the one on trial. You should remember that you are a lesser god and if not for me you nor anyone else here could of been made possible. Also you should remember just because you think your one of the Olympians does not make it so. I accept that I am of older Generation and have no throne upon the Glorius Mountain my grandchildren and great grandchildren reside because I unlike you know my place.&quot;<br>
<br>
Gaia sat there, calm. She would not let her anger get to her, because that's exactly what Hypnos wanted. <p>~*-:¦:-*~Gaia: Greek Goddess of Earth~*-:¦:-*~ <BR>-§Mother Earth§-¤Mother of the Titans¤-¥Mother of All Creation¥-</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uposeidonkofc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Poseidonkofc</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Golden Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 317<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(7/12/02 12:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=260.topic&index=40>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://web.uvic.ca/grs/bowman/myth/images/haifa/h89.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Earthy One</span><hr size=1> Beings began to appear here and there, those whom were called for and those who were quite uncalled for. Poseidon acknowledged all those for whom had given him a greeting willingly or unwillingly. Before the sea god did anything he let a few skirmishes and a few mistakes pass him by.<br>
<br>
Sitting there regally on his throne in an uncommonly calm demeanor Poseidon watched as before his very eyes and presence Hypnos insulted his dignity and not just once but many a time. First without any consent to do so, Hypnos weaved his magics on his servants and blatantly dropped them before the gods feet, all in a drows. Then Hypnos came in a prideful way to a trail, as if he were in his pride invincible, though he did not know how much he was not so compared to the might and main of the elder Gods , those who had founded the Olympian Gods. And lastly he sought to make dissention between Poseidon and his own grandmother, one whom he would never willingly seek to harm or upset.<br>
<br>
The powerful God of the sea raised his hand and called for silence. His sea blue eyes rested on Hypnos, the aura of sleep having no effect whatsoever on the god, though if Hypnos willed it so it could. He seemed to be like his brother Zeus now, the cool tempered one with his head straight on his shoulders.<br>
<br>
As he rose the shadow he left behind seemed to remain in his chair, his height seemed to change yet remained the same, but this was only because of the build up of stress within him. Hypnos had struck a cord and there was no telling when the vocalization of  that struck cord would ring loud. He stood before Hypnos, looking down on the thing that he detested, alive and breathing before him and he opened his mouth with his glaring eyes and spoke to the god in a more than moderate tone of voice.<br>
<br>
&quot;You Hypnos have come to be trailed. Do not fret, do not make a show of yourself. You sleep god are standing in the prescence of me, Poseidon, Zeus' equal in dignity and my rights will not be belied by YOU or any immortal here&quot; he said with a deep and calm voice.   <br>
<br>
&quot;Do not undermine the power of the Gods, for you a god yourself have incited a God or gods anger here this day and you seem to forget that none of the Olympians can you contend with and in a court you shall mind your scrupples. And you seem to forget that I can if I would crush you like a gnat, do not be the one this day to be the example to all Gods that a god can and may die. Now if there is nothing further this trail shall begin and you shall defend yourself and call whom you will in you defence, pertaining to your outrageous behavior.&quot;<br>
<br>
The god turned on his heels and nodded to Apollo, galring back at Hypnos for an instant and then plopping down in his throne-like chair.<br>
<br>
